<p><a href="http://science.nbcnews.com/_news/2013/03/19/17373981-parasitic-wasp-named-kiddo-after-kill-bill-assassin?lite"><img align="left" border="0" src="http://msnbcmedia.msn.com/j/MSNBC/Components/Photo/_new/bill-m--fink42208F69-EE7E-8173-7E2E-92F88EACA974.thumb.jpg" alt="A new species of parasitic wasp with a lethal lifestyle is taking its name from assassin Beatrix Kiddo, the heroine played by Uma Thurman in Quentin Tarantino's &quot;Kill Bill&quot; films." style="margin:0 5px 5px 0" /></a>A new species of parasitic wasp with a lethal lifestyle is taking its name from assassin Beatrix Kiddo, the heroine played by Uma Thurman in Quentin Tarantino's "Kill Bill" films.</p><br clear="all" />
<li><a href='http://www.nbcnews.com/technology/gadgetbox/update-your-iphone-now-fix-passcode-vulnerability-1C8932493' target="_blank">Update your iPhone now to fix a passcode vulnerability</a><br />
